    "recap_headline": "Washington State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SAN MARCOS, Texas (March 8, 2026)\n\u2013 Washington State put two runners on in the ninth inning but the rally was held off by the Texas State bullpen for a 4-3 Bobcat win at Bobcat Ballpark Sunday afternoon.\nWashington State (6-9) leadoff hitter\nTrevor Smith\nreached base three times including a pair of RBI-singles but just missed a go-ahead grand slam after his seventh inning RBI-single hit halfway up the right field wall.\nDane Chavez\nalso reached base three times with a single, a pair of walks and two runs scored while\nGavin Roy\nadded a pair of singles and a walk.\nCougar pitching combined for 10 strikeouts but Texas State (12-3) used a second-inning two-run homer and runs in the fifth and sixth innings to clinch the series. WSU combined to leave nine runners on base.\nKEY MOMENTS OF THE GAME\nTexas State took a 2-0 with an opposite-field two-run home run in the second inning.\nThe Cougars made it a one-run game in after Smith's RBI-single to left field in the fifth inning but left the bases loaded to end the frame. Texas State answered with a run of their own in the bottom of the inning and later added another RBI-single in the sixth for a 4-1 advantage.\nIn the seventh, Alexandre Gigu\u00e8re led off with a line drove single to left, Chavez and Roy followed with bunt singles to load the bases. Smith nearly gave the Cougars the lead with a long drive to right field but it hit half way up the wall and was held to an RBI-single. One batter later,\nMax Hartman's\nRBI-fielder's choice groundout to shortstop made it a one-run game.\nIn the ninth, Smith and pinch-hitter\nCam Macleod\nwere both hit by pitches two outs but Hartman's hard-hit groundball was snagged by the second baseman who fired to first for the final out.\nINSIDE THE BOX SCORE\nDane Chavez\nwalked in the 3\nrd\ninning, has reached base in 8 straight games\nTrevor Smith's\nRBI-single in 5\nth\nextended his on-base streak to 12 games\nGavin Derr\nstarted, allowed 2 earned runs on 3 hits in 3 innings\nKaden Wickersham\nstruck out 2 in a scoreless 7\nth\ninning\nTrevor Stowe\nstruck out 2 in a scoreless 8\nth\ninning\nON DEC\nK\nWSU opens Mountain West Conference play with a three-game series at San Diego State beginning Friday."
